[{"content":"# ðŸ’Ž iDX Starter\n## *DOPE IDE*\n* **JavaScript**\n* **JSX**\n* **Imports from NPM like React, ReactDOM, Redux, and more**\n\n## Installation\n`$ npx colsidx serve`","type":"text","id":"97gk8"},{"content":"# Builtin `show()` function!\n**iDX comes with this cool function that can render strings, numbers, arrays, objects and more ðŸ”¥**\n\nHere's `show()` in action:","type":"text","id":"z4zr6"},{"content":"show(<h1 style={{ color: '#4285F4' }}>COLSON uses NEOVIM</h1>);","type":"code","id":"cazua"},{"content":"show(1111);","type":"code","id":"at39x"},{"content":"const AppMain = () => {\n  return <h1 style={{ color: '#4285F4' }}>Private Jet</h1>;\n};\n\nshow(<AppMain />);","type":"code","id":"nqwu6"},{"content":"const car = {\n  1: 'Lamborghini',\n  2: 'Rolls Royce',\n  3: 'Ferrari',\n  4: 'McLaren',\n  5: 'Mercedes',\n  6: 'Aston Martin',\n};\n\nshow(car);","type":"code","id":"bl8x1"},{"content":"const users = [\n  { id: 1, name: 'Colson' },\n  { id: 2, name: 'Google' },\n  { id: 3, name: 'Netflix' },\n];\n\nshow(users);","type":"code","id":"8pt09"},{"content":"# Supports `NPM` packages ðŸ”¥","type":"text","id":"wchen"},{"content":"import React from 'react';\nimport ReactDOM from 'react-dom/client';\n\nconst App = () => {\n  return <h1 style={{ color: '#4285F4' }}>ðŸ’Ž COLSON</h1>;\n};\n\nconst root = ReactDOM.createRoot(document.querySelector('#root'));\nroot.render(<App />);","type":"code","id":"v2qx2"},{"content":"# Cumulative code execution\n\n**Note: Its executing above instance of code**","type":"text","id":"s2jsm"},{"content":"const Mansion = () => {\n  return <h1 style={{ color: '#4285F4' }}>ðŸ’Ž Private Mansion</h1>;\n};","type":"code","id":"6g0vp"},{"content":"const Lamborghini = () => {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <h1 style={{ color: '#4285F4' }}>ðŸ’Ž Lamborghini</h1>;\n    </div>\n  );\n};","type":"code","id":"po0ys"},{"content":"**Noticed**! We don't have to use: \n`import React from 'react';`\n`import React from 'react-dom/client'`; Because we've done that above.","type":"text","id":"o0sgu"},{"content":"const AppExotic = () => {\n  return (\n    <div>\n      <h1 style={{ color: '#4285F4' }}>ðŸ’Ž COLSON WEALTH</h1>\n      <Mansion />\n      <Lamborghini />\n    </div>\n  );\n};\n\nroot.render(<AppExotic />);","type":"code","id":"mph9z"},{"content":"# `FINAL NOTE`\nThe default file that opens is `adventOfCode.js`. <br/>\nYou can create new documentation for yourself about things you're learning, coding snippets and more using:<br/>\n`$ colsidx serve <new-filename>`\n\nAnother thing is the default port which is 4004. It can be changed with:\n`$ colsidx serve -p 4009`<br />\n\nMultiple files can be opened:\n\n`$ colsidx serve -p 4006 higherOrderComponents.js` <br/>\n`$ colsidx serve -p 4007  authentication.js`<br/>\n`$ colsidx serve -p -4008 decorators.js`<br/>\n\nThat's it :)\n\n**Thanks again, for installing this app. It's Colson and I hope this will be very useful to you in your daily life!**\n<br/>\nPeace!!","type":"text","id":"2a5l6"}]